        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:14PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Fox, or 17 miles northwest of John Day, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fox.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
